commit.message:
Removed "Ask" option from lid and idle watchers (#380)

Because it didn't make sense in them.

The "Ask" option is kept untouched in the battery and power watchers.

Closes https://github.com/lxqt/lxqt-powermanagement/issues/254

commit.message:
Also suspend screensaver when idle watcher is enabled (#376)

Without this, the screensaver timeout will kick in and interfere with our daemon. The suspension will be reverted when the idle watcher is disabled or the daemon is stopped.

Fixes https://github.com/lxqt/lxqt-powermanagement/issues/374 completely

commit.message:
Override DPMS on enabling idleness watcher (#375)

* Override DPMS on enabling idleness watcher

The patch disables DPMS when the idle watcher is enabled, by giving it three zero values, as some LXQt users might have done manually (me included).

It also restores its original timeouts when the idle watcher is disabled.

Fixes https://github.com/lxqt/lxqt-powermanagement/issues/374

* Also let `liblxqt` handle quit signals

This is especially needed for restoring DPMS timeouts when the daemon is stopped inside a session.

Override DPMS on enabling idleness watcher (#375)

* Override DPMS on enabling idleness watcher

The patch disables DPMS when the idle watcher is enabled, by giving it three zero values, as some LXQt users might have done manually (me included).

It also restores its original timeouts when the idle watcher is disabled.

Fixes https://github.com/lxqt/lxqt-powermanagement/issues/374

* Also let `liblxqt` handle quit signals

This is especially needed for restoring DPMS timeouts when the daemon is stopped inside a session.
